A: James runs **3 sprints** **3 times a week**.  
Each sprint is **60 meters**.

### Step 1: Calculate meters per day
$$
3 \text{ sprints/day} \times 60 \text{ meters/sprint} = 180 \text{ meters/day}
$$

### Step 2: Calculate total meters per week
$$
180 \text{ meters/day} \times 3 \text{ days/week} = 

